President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has submitted a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13664 regarding South Sudan will continue beyond April 3, 2023. The President cites ongoing threats to peace, security, and stability in South Sudan and the surrounding region, including violence, atrocities, human rights abuses, the use of child soldiers, attacks on peacekeepers, and obstruction of humanitarian operations. Consequently, President Biden has determined that it is necessary to maintain the national emergency in relation to South Sudan. The notice was sent to the Federal Register for publication on March 29, 2023.